Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.92,0:02:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,金星或許曾是一個天堂\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The planet Venus, which once may have seemed like a heaven,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.59,0:02:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,但現在卻是一個地獄\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}turned into a kind of hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.42,0:02:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,造成這個差異的原因是因為有一些微妙的自然平衡被打破了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The difference between the two can be a delicate balance,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.72,0:03:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,而且是比你想像中更為微妙的關係\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}far more delicate than you might imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.18,0:03:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,這個平衡一旦被打破 就再也無法挽回\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Once things began to unravel, there was no way back.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.06,0:03:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是金星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is what Venus,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.93,0:03:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,距離我們最近的行星 今天看上去的樣子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}our nearest planetary neighbor, looks like today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.11,0:03:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,金星上的海洋已經消失很久了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Venus's oceans are long gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.53,0:03:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,星球的表面現在比燒烤爐還要燙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The surface is hotter than a broiling oven,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.30,0:03:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,熱得足以融化鉛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}hot enough to melt lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.96,0:03:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,為什麼呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.17,0:03:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,你也許認為這是因為金星到太陽的距離要比地球少30%\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You might think it's because Venus is 30% closer to the Sun than the Earth is,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.38,0:03:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,但這不是真正的原因\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but that's not the reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.88,0:03:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,金星現在完全被硫酸雲覆蓋著\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Venus is completely covered by clouds of sulfuric acid
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.51,0:03:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,幾乎沒有陽光可以照射到它的表面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that keep almost all the sunlight from reaching the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.89,0:03:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,按理來說這應該讓金星比地球更寒冷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That ought to make Venus much colder than the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.89,0:03:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,但為何金星會如此的灼熱？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So why is Venus scorching hot?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.83,0:03:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,那是因為有小部分的陽光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's because the small amount of sunlight
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.96,0:03:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,穿過雲層抵達了地面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that trickles in through the clouds to reach the surface
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.03,0:03:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,卻沒能反射回去\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}can't get back out again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.17,0:04:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,能量不能散發是由於濃密的大氣阻隔\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The flow of energy is blocked by a dense atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.04,0:04:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,那就是二氧化碳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of carbon dioxide.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.70,0:04:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,二氧化碳簡稱CO2\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That carbon dioxide gas-- or CO2 for short--
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.68,0:04:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,它就像毯子一樣阻止熱量的散發\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}acts like a smothering blanket to keep the heat in.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.01,0:04:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,沒人在金星上燒煤\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No one is burning coal
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.81,0:04:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,或是開著大馬力的汽車在上面逛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}or driving big gas-guzzlers on Venus.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.48,0:04:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,自然能滅掉環境的平衡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Nature can destroy an environment
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.35,0:04:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,而不需要借助人的力量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}without any help from intelligent life.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.09,0:04:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,金星現在正處於強烈的溫室效應中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Venus is in the grip of a runaway greenhouse effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.69,0:04:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,為什麼我們現在像是在一個碗裏？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Why does it look like we're inside a bowl?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.60,0:04:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,那是因為濃密的大氣壓力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's due to the intense atmospheric pressure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.53,0:04:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,這是金星13號的殘骸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's the wreck of Venera 13.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.44,0:04:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,1982年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In 1982, the scientists and engineers
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.17,0:04:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,蘇聯的科學家與工程師們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of what was then the Soviet Union
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.58,0:04:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,成功地將這艘探測器送到了金星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}successfully landed this spacecraft on Venus.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.38,0:04:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,他們設法讓飛船\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They managed to keep it refrigerated
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.61,0:04:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,保持了2個小時以上的冷凍狀態\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for overtwo hours,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.35,0:04:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,讓它能給四周拍照\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}so it could photograph its surroundings...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.29,0:04:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,並將照片傳回了地球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and transmit the images back to Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.79,0:04:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,隨後飛船上的電子設備就燒燬了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}before the on-board electronics were fried.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.93,0:05:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,金星與地球在誕生初期具有相同的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Venus and Earth started out with about the same amount
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.40,0:05:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,碳含量 但兩個星球卻被推上了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of carbon, but the two worlds were propelled
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.20,0:05:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,截然不同的發展道路\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}along radically different paths,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.57,0:05:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,碳元素在其中起到了決定性的作用\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and carbon was the decisive element in both stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.08,0:05:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,在金星 幾乎所有的大氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}On Venus, it's almost all in the form of gas--
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.15,0:05:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,都由二氧化碳組成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}carbon dioxide-- in the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.49,0:05:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,地球上大部分的碳已經在久遠的年代中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Most of the carbon on Earth has been stored for eons
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.49,0:05:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,以碳酸鹽巖的形式被儲存起來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in solid vaults of carbonate rock,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.26,0:05:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,就像這一塊 它就是其中一種形式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}like this one, part of a chain that forms
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.77,0:05:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是著名的多佛海岸白色懸崖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the celebrated White Cliffs of Dover,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.53,0:05:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,它位於英吉利海峽的邊上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}right on the English Channel.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.87,0:05:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,是哪位巨人修建了這樣的世界奇觀？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What titan built this wonder of the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.06,0:06:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,那是一種比針頭還要小1000倍的生物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A creature a thousand times smaller than a pinhead.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.56,0:06:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,數以萬億計\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Trillions of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.57,0:06:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,它叫單細胞藻類\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}One-celled algae.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.87,0:06:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,火山將二氧化碳送入大氣後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Volcanoes supply carbon dioxide to the atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.24,0:06:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,海洋將它緩慢地吸收\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the oceans slowly absorb it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.45,0:06:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,這個過程要延續好幾百萬年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Working over the course of millions of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.12,0:06:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,先是微小的藻類吸收了二氧化碳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the microscopic algae harvested the carbon dioxide
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.29,0:06:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,並將它轉化為這些小貝殼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and turned it into these tiny shells.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.02,0:06:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,日積月累 最終沉積為白堊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They accumulated in thick deposits of chalk,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.56,0:06:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我們也稱之為石灰岩 它積聚在海床上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}or limestone, on the ocean floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.23,0:06:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,最終 永不停息的地殼運動將海床推起\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Later, the restless Earth pushed up the sea floor
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.63,0:06:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,將它塑造成這些巨大的懸崖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and carved out these massive cliffs.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.97,0:06:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,其他的海洋生物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Other marine creatures
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.11,0:06:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,用二氧化碳建造了巨大的珊瑚礁\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}took in carbon dioxide to build enormous coral reefs.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.91,0:06:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,海洋也可以把溶解的二氧化碳轉換為石灰岩\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And the oceans converted dissolved CO2 into limestone
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.88,0:06:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,而不需要生物的幫助\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}even without any help from life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.95,0:07:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,最終 只有微量的二氧化碳氣體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}As a result, only a trace amount was left as a gas
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.59,0:07:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,留在了地球的大氣中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in Earth's atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.12,0:07:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,還不到每百分之一中的三百分之一\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Not even three-hundredths of one percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.26,0:07:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,相當於每1萬個分子中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Think of it-- fewer than three molecules
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.26,0:07:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,只有不到3個分子保留下來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}out of every ten thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.40,0:07:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,而這幾個分子就是最關鍵的因素\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And yet, it makes the critical difference
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.84,0:07:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,決定了地球是生命的樂土還是荒蕪之地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}between a barren wasteland and a garden of life on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.98,0:07:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,要是一點二氧化碳都沒有\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}With no CO2 at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.95,0:07:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,地球將會被冰凍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the Earth would be frozen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.78,0:07:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,可要是二氧化碳的數量再多一倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And with twice as many,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.82,0:07:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,也就是像前面所說的 每1萬個分子中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we're still talking about only six molecules
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.79,0:07:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,有6個分子保留下來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}out of ten thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.42,0:07:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,令人不安的炎熱就會襲來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Things would get uncomfortably hot
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.52,0:07:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,給人類帶來一系列的問題\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and cause us some serious problems...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.39,0:07:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,不過還不會像金星那麼熱 一點都不會\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but never as hot as Venus; not even close.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.13,0:07:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,在好幾百萬年前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That planet lost its ocean to space
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.83,0:07:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,這個行星上的海洋就已經消失到太空中了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}billions of years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.17,0:07:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有了海洋 它就沒有辦法從空氣中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Without an ocean, it had no way to capture CO2
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.41,0:07:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,捕獲二氧化碳 並將它存儲為礦物質\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from the atmosphere and store it as a mineral.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.13,0:07:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,從噴發的火山中產生的二氧化碳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The CO2 from erupting volcanoes
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.28,0:07:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,不斷地積累\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}just continued to build up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.95,0:08:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,時至今日 金星上的大氣要比地球重90倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Today, that atmosphere is 90 times heavier than ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.35,0:08:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,幾乎全部由灼熱的二氧化碳氣體組成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Almost all of it is heat-trapping carbon dioxide.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.72,0:08:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是為什麼金星會變成如此殘酷的地獄\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's why Venus is such a ferocious inferno
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.09,0:08:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,生命無法在此扎根的原因\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}so hostile to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.73,0:08:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,地球則恰恰與此相反\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Earth, in stunning contrast,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.90,0:08:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,它是有生命的星球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.60,0:08:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,它會呼吸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It breathes...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.20,0:08:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,不過很緩慢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but very slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.44,0:08:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,1年才能完成1次呼吸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A single breath takes a whole year.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.78,0:08:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,森林裏包含了地球上大部分的生命\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The forests contain most of Earth's life,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.08,0:08:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,大部分的森林都位於北半球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and most forests are in the Northern Hemisphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.98,0:08:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,當北半球的春季到來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When spring comes to the north,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.15,0:08:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,森林吸入空氣中的二氧化碳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the forests inhale carbon dioxide from the air
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.22,0:08:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,並隨之生長 將大地鋪滿綠色\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and grow, turning the land green.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.42,0:08:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,大氣中的二氧化碳含量隨之下降\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The amount of CO2 in the atmosphere goes down.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.49,0:08:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,秋天降臨 植物落葉 隨之枯萎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When fall comes and the plants drop their leaves, they decay,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.06,0:08:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,將二氧化碳呼出到大氣中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}exhaling the carbon dioxide back into the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.00,0:08:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,同樣的過程也會發生在南半球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The same thing happens in the Southern Hemisphere
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.64,0:08:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,只是季節是相反的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}at the opposite time of the year.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.97,0:08:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,但南半球大部分是海洋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But the Southern Hemisphere is mostly ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.98,0:08:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,因此 是北半球的森林\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So it's the forests of the north
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.01,0:09:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,控制了全球每年二氧化碳含量的變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that control the annual changes in the global CO2.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.51,0:09:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,地球已經像這樣呼吸了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Earth has been breathing like this
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.32,0:09:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,數千萬年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for tens of millions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.45,0:09:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,從沒有人注意到這一點 直到1958年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But nobody noticed until 1958,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.42,0:09:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,有一位海洋學家叫查爾斯•戴維•基林\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when an oceanographer named Charles David Keeling
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.59,0:09:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,他設計了一種方法 可以精確地測量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}devised a way to accurately measure
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.63,0:09:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,空氣中二氧化碳的含量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the amount of carbon dioxide in the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.97,0:09:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,基林發現了地球的細微呼吸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Keeling discovered the Earth's exquisite respiration.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.81,0:09:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,但他也發現了一些令人震驚的事實\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But he also discovered something shocking--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.35,0:09:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,有一個數字在以人類歷史上前所未有的速度上升\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a rapid rise, unprecedented in human history,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.02,0:09:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,那就是空氣中二氧化碳的整體水平\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the overall level of CO2,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.59,0:09:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,至今這個變化還一直在繼續\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}one that has continued ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.43,0:09:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,二氧化碳水平的驚人變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's a striking departure from the CO2 levels that prevailed
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.97,0:09:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,始於農業與文明的興起時期\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}during the rise of agriculture and civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.27,0:09:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,實際上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In fact, the Earth has seen nothing like it
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.84,0:09:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,地球在過去的300萬年不是這個樣子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for three million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.31,0:10:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,我們為何如此確信\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14} How can we be so sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.21,0:10:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,證據就記錄在水裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The evidence is written in water.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.65,0:10:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,地球保存著一份詳細的日記\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Earth keeps a detailed diary
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.62,0:10:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,它就寫在過去下的雪裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}written in the snows of yesteryear.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.96,0:10:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,氣候科學家們鑽出冰芯\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Climate scientists have drilled ice cores
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.00,0:10:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,從格林蘭島和南極洲的冰川深處\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from the depths of glaciers in Greenland and Antarctica.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.67,0:10:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,遠古的空氣被困在了冰層裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The ice layers have ancient air trapped inside them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.17,0:10:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,我們可以閱讀到地球大氣的完整記錄\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We can read the unbroken record of Earth's atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.78,0:10:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,一直可以追溯到8萬年前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that extends back over the last 800,000 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.25,0:10:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,在以往的所有時間內\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In all that time,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.52,0:10:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,大氣中的二氧化碳數值從沒有超過\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the amount of carbon dioxide in the air never rose
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.12,0:10:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,每百分之一的空氣中含有三百分之一的二氧化碳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}above three-hundredths of one percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.42,0:10:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,但到了二十世紀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That is, until the turn of the 20th century.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.19,0:10:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,它就開始穩定而迅速的上升並保持至今\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And it's been going up steadily and rapidly ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.40,0:10:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,現在這個數值\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's now more than 40% higher
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.93,0:10:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,已經比工業革命前高出了40%\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}than before the Industrial Revolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.20,0:10:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,通過燃燒煤 石油和煤氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}By burning coal, oil and gas,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.40,0:11:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,人類文明在釋放出二氧化碳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}our civilization is exhaling carbon dioxide
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.74,0:11:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,遠遠超過了地球所能吸收的速度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}much faster than Earth can absorb it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.04,0:11:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,因此大氣中的二氧化碳在不斷積累\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So CO2 is building up in the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.55,0:11:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,這個星球在升溫\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The planet is heating up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.78,0:11:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,每一個發熱的物體都能輻射出某種我們肉眼看不見的光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Every warm object radiates a kind of light we can't see with the naked eye--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.89,0:11:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,那就是熱紅外線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}thermal infrared light.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.79,0:11:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,即使在黑暗中 我們的身體也能散發出不可見的熱輻射\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We all glow with invisible heat radiation, even in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.33,0:11:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,如果用紅外線觀察地球 它就是這個樣子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is what the Earth looks like in the infrared.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.26,0:11:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,你看到的是行星本身的發熱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You're seeing the planet's own body heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.07,0:11:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,當陽光照射到地面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Incoming light from the Sun hits the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.81,0:11:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,地球本身會吸收大部分的能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Earth absorbs much of that energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.25,0:11:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,讓地球升溫\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which heats the planet up
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.01,0:11:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,從而讓地表發出紅外線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and makes the surface glow in infrared light.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.08,0:11:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,但空氣中的二氧化碳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But the carbon dioxide in the atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.49,0:11:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,又會吸收散發出的大部分熱量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}absorbs most of that outgoing heat radiation,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.36,0:11:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,把這些熱量的大部分又傳回地面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}sending much of it right back to the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.16,0:11:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,讓地球變得更熱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This makes the planet even warmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.26,0:11:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是所謂的溫室效應\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's all there is to the greenhouse effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.60,0:12:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,它的基本物理原理\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's basic physics,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.27,0:12:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,就在於把流動的能量保存下來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}just bookkeeping of the energy flow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.67,0:12:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,關於它沒什麼好爭議的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's nothing controversial about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.37,0:12:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,如果大氣中一點二氧化碳都沒有\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If we didn't have any carbon dioxide in our atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.27,0:12:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,地球就會變成一個大雪球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the Earth would just be a great big snowball,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.44,0:12:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,人類也就不會存在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and we wouldn't be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.05,0:12:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,因此 輕度的溫室效應是件好事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So, a little greenhouse effect is a good thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.82,0:12:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,可它要是變大 就會造成氣候的不穩定\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But a big one can destabilize the climate
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.92,0:12:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,甚至毀掉人類的生存方式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and wreck our way of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.06,0:12:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 但我們怎麼知道人類是問題的根源？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}All right... but how do we know that we're the problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.16,0:12:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,也許是地球本身導致二氧化碳的增加\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Maybe the Earth itself is causing the rise in CO2.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.00,0:12:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,也許和煤與石油的燃燒無關\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Maybe it has nothing to do with the coal and oil we burn.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.40,0:12:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,或許是那些該死的火山\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Maybe it's those damn volcanoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.74,0:12:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,每隔幾年 西西里島的埃特納火山就會噴發\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Every few years, Mount Etna, in Sicily, blows its stack.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.01,0:12:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,每次的大規模噴發都會把幾百萬噸二氧化碳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Each big eruption sends millions of tons of CO2
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.88,0:12:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,送入空氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.78,0:12:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我們把\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Now, combine that with the output
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.29,0:12:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,地球上所有的火山噴發合計起來的話\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of all the other volcanic activity on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.62,0:12:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,讓我們按最大數量進行科學預測\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Let's take the largest scientific estimate--
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.79,0:13:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,每年大概會有5億噸二氧化碳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}about 500 million tons of volcanic CO2
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.63,0:13:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,被送入空氣中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}entering the atmosphere ever year.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.80,0:13:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,聽上去很多 對不對？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Sounds like a lot, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.57,0:13:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,可這個數值還不到人類每年產生的二氧化碳數量的2%\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But that's not even two percent of the 30 billion tons of CO2
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.10,0:13:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,那就是1年300億噸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that our civilization is cranking out every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.14,0:13:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,而且 還有個很有趣的現象\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And, funny thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.04,0:13:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,大氣中二氧化碳的增加量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the measured increase in CO2 in the atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.91,0:13:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,與我們所知的 即是通過燃燒煤 石油和煤氣產生的二氧化碳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}tallies with the known amount we're dumping there
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.78,0:13:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,剛好相同\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}by burning coal, oil and gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.79,0:13:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,火山產生的二氧化碳有一個明顯的特徵\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Volcanic CO2 has a distinct signature--
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.89,0:13:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,與化石燃料燃燒時產生的二氧化碳相比\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it's slightly heavier than the kind produced
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.56,0:13:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,它要稍微重一些\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}by burning fossil fuels.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.96,0:13:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我們可以分辨出這兩者的差別\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We can tell the difference between the two
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.83,0:13:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,通過對它們進行原子級別的檢驗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when we examine them at the atomic level.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.47,0:13:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,檢驗結果很明顯證實 空氣中增加的二氧化碳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's clear that the increased CO2 in the air
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.07,0:13:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,不是來自火山\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is not from volcanoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.34,0:13:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,更重要的是 氣候變暖的程度與\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What's more, the observed warming is as much as predicted
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.67,0:13:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,空氣中二氧化碳增加的程度差不多\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from the measured increase in carbon dioxide.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.81,0:13:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,這兩者緊密關聯\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's a pretty tight case.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.75,0:13:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,人類排放二氧化碳的證據都在這上面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our fingerprints are all over this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.28,0:14:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,每年30億噸二氧化碳到底有多少?\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How much is 30 billion tons of CO2 per year?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.69,0:14:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我們把它壓成一個固體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If you compressed it into solid form,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.15,0:14:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,它的體積就會和\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it would occupy about the same volume
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.29,0:14:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,多佛海岸的白色懸崖差不多\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as the White Cliffs of Dover.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.66,0:14:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是我們每年排放到空氣中的二氧化碳的數量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And we're adding that much CO2 to the air every year,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.10,0:14:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,永無休止 年復一年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}relentlessly, year after year.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.67,0:14:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,很不幸的是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Unlucky for us, the main waste product
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.87,0:14:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,人類文明產生的主要垃圾產品不是物質\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of our civilization is not just any substance.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.31,0:14:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,而是能對全球氣候調節產生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It happens to be the chief climate-regulating gas
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.84,0:14:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,恆溫效果的毒氣 年年如此\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of our global thermostat, year in, year out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.55,0:14:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,過多的二氧化碳就相當於看不見的毒氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Too bad CO2 is an invisible gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.92,0:14:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我們能看到它……\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Maybe if we could see it...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.56,0:14:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我們的眼睛能感應到二氧化碳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If our eyes were sensitive to CO2--
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.76,0:14:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,也許在宇宙中有這樣的生物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and perhaps there are such beings in the cosmos--
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.76,0:14:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我們能看見二氧化碳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}if we could see all that carbon dioxide,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.23,0:14:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,那就沒有人能否定這一切\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}then we would overcome the denial
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.27,0:14:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,並充分瞭解到人類對大氣的嚴重影響\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and grasp the magnitude of our impact on the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.09,0:15:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,但全球變暖的證據\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But the evidence that the world is getting warmer
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.32,0:15:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,就在我們身邊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is all around us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.26,0:15:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,首先讓我們檢查一下\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For starters, let's just check the thermometers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.36,0:15:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,世界各地氣象站的溫度計\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Weather stations around the world
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.36,0:15:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,自1880年代起\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}have been keeping reliable temperature records
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.33,0:15:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,它們一直保存著可靠的溫度記錄\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}since the 1880s,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.03,0:15:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,美國宇航局用這些數據編製了一幅地圖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and NASA has used the data to compile a map
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.17,0:15:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,地圖涵蓋了所有的時間段\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}tracking the average temperatures
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.87,0:15:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,用作跟蹤世界各地平均氣溫的變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}around the world through time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.24,0:15:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,黃色意味著溫度較高\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Yellow means warmer temperatures
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.94,0:15:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,高於1880年代任何地區的平均水平\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}than the average, for any region in the 1880s.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.95,0:15:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,橙色意味著炎熱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Orange means hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.69,0:15:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,紅色意味著比炎熱更熱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And red means hotter.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.02,0:15:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,世界已經變得比19世紀更溫暖了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The world is warmer than it was in the 19th century.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.26,0:15:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,那時 全球各地的氣溫是有史以來最均衡的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Back then, at the greatest fair the world has ever seen,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.97,0:15:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,一位被遺忘的天才曾設想了一個解決問題的方案\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a forgotten genius demonstrated the solution to this problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.60,0:15:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,跟我來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.33,0:16:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,曾經有這樣一個世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Once there was a world
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.97,0:16:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,它不太熱也不太冷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that was not too hot and not too cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.84,0:16:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,溫度適中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was just right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.30,0:16:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,然後有一天 這裏的人們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Then there came a time when the life it sustained
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.94,0:16:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,開始注意到他們可愛的地球在發生變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}began to notice our lovely planet was changing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.31,0:16:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,這並不是說我們沒有預見到它的到來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And it's not as if we didn't see it coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.20,0:16:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}三十一. 關於碳酸空氣中對地面溫度的影響
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.58,0:16:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,早在1896年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}As far back as 1896,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.75,0:16:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,瑞典科學家斯凡特•阿倫尼斯\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the Swedish scientist Svante Arrhenius
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.66,0:16:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,通過計算發現 如果大氣中的二氧化碳含量再增加1倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}calculated that doubling the amount
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.02,0:16:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}大氣就如溫室一般
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.06,0:16:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,就能讓北極的冰融化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of CO2 in the atmosphere would melt the Arctic ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.23,0:16:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,到了1930年代 美國物理學家E.O.赫爾伯特\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In the 1930s, the American physicist E. O. Hulburt,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.80,0:16:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,在海軍實驗室裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}at the Naval Research Laboratory,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.74,0:16:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,確認了這個結果\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}confirmed that result.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.74,0:16:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}二氧化碳令地球變熱
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.57,0:16:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,到那時為止 這一切還依然是理論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So far, it was still just theoretical.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.78,0:16:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,隨後 英國工程師蓋•卡倫德\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But then, the English engineer Guy Callendar
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.89,0:17:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}人為排放二氧化碳對於氣溫的影響
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.01,0:17:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,把這些證據結合起來 向人們展示\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}assembled the evidence to show
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.15,0:17:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,二氧化碳含量與全球平均氣溫\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that both the CO2 and the average global temperature
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.42,0:17:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,都在不斷上升中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}were actually increasing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.92,0:17:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,就算是現在 人們也可能在無意中改變了全球氣候\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Even now, man may be unwittingly changing the world's climate
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.29,0:17:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,通過文明產生的廢棄物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}through the waste products of his civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.59,0:17:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,由於人類通過工廠與汽車的排放\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Due to our release, through factories
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.60,0:17:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,每年有超過\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and automobiles every year, of more than
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.30,0:17:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,60億噸的二氧化碳產生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}six billion tons of carbon dioxide,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.60,0:17:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,讓空氣吸收了更多來自於太陽的熱量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which helps air absorb heat from the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.04,0:17:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,大氣變得越來越熱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}our atmosphere seems to be getting warmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.81,0:17:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,這是不是件壞事?\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14} This is bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.68,0:17:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,嗯 通過計算表明\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Well, it's been calculated, a few degrees rise
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.38,0:17:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,地球溫度的輕微升高\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the Earth's temperature
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.68,0:17:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,會讓地球兩極的冰帽熔化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}would melt the polar ice caps.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.10,0:17:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}二氧化碳與氣候\N"當前的理論 假設了二氧化碳會調節地球的溫度 這就產生了一個很有趣的問題：\N人類的活動如何影響未來的氣候呢？"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.49,0:17:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,1960年 卡爾•薩根在他的博士論文裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In 1960,Carl Sagan's PhD thesis
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.36,0:17:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,第一次計算了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}included the first calculation
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.23,0:17:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,金星上失控的溫室效應\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the runaway greenhouse effect on Venus.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.86,0:17:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,這是他職業興趣的一個部分\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This was part of a career-long interest
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.73,0:17:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,對於行星大氣 包括我們的星球的興趣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the atmospheres of the planets, including our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.83,0:17:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}氣候變化:我們正處於地球變暖的邊緣嗎?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.90,0:17:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}大氣中增加的二氧化碳對氣候的影響
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.87,0:17:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,在1980製作的最初那部宇宙系列片中 卡爾•薩根警告說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In the original Cosmos series, in 1980, Carl Sagan warned...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.04,0:17:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,"我們正在釋放大量的二氧化碳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We are releasing vast quantities of carbon dioxide,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.37,0:18:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,加劇了溫室效應\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}increasing the greenhouse effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.24,0:18:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,用不了多久\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It may not take much
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.98,0:18:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,地球的氣候就會失去平衡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to destabilize the Earth's climate,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.38,0:18:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,把我們在宇宙中這唯一的家園 像天堂一樣的地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to convert this heaven, our only home in the cosmos,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.85,0:18:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,變為人間地獄"\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into a kind of hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.13,0:18:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,卡爾說過這些話之後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Since Carl spoke those words,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.36,0:18:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,我們還在繼續加重大氣的負擔\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we've burdened the atmosphere of our world with an additional
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.46,0:18:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,每年又多增加了4千億噸二氧化碳的排放\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}400 billion tons of carbon dioxide.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.97,0:18:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我們不改變這個現狀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If we don't change our ways,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.87,0:18:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,我們未來的孩子們將會面對一個什麼樣的星球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}what will the planet be like in our children's future?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.64,0:18:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,根據科學研究項目的結果\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Based on scientific projections,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.98,0:18:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我們繼續保持著現有的經濟模式不變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}if we just keep on doing business as usual,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.85,0:18:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的子孫將會面對艱險的未來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}our kids are in for a rough ride.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.25,0:18:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,致命的熱浪 破紀錄的乾旱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Killer heat waves, record droughts,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.39,0:18:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,不斷升高的海平面 大規模的物種滅絕\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}rising sea levels, mass extinction of species.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.22,0:18:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我們曾從前人手中繼承了一個富饒的世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We inherited a bountiful world
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.73,0:18:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,氣候相對穩定\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}made possible by a relatively stable climate.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.89,0:18:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,農業繁榮 文明興盛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Agriculture and civilization flourished
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.26,0:18:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,延續了千年之久\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.23,0:19:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,可現在 人類的冷漠與貪婪把這一切推向了危險的境地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And now, our carelessness and greed put all of that at risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.91,0:19:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 如果科學家們有那麼厲害\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Okay, so if we scientists are so good
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.11,0:19:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,可以作出關於氣候的如此長遠的可怕預測\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}at making these dire, long-term predictions about the climate,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.11,0:19:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,那為什麼就不能把天氣測准一點呢?\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How come we're so lousy about predicting the weather?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.02,0:19:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,還有 今年我家鄉的冬天特別寒冷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Besides, this year, we had a colder winter in my town.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.89,0:19:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的科學家知不知道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For all us scientists know,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.85,0:19:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,說不定我們現在面對的是全球變冷呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we could be in for global cooling.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.76,0:19:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,天氣和氣候是不同的兩個概念\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Here's the difference between weather and climate...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.69,0:19:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,天氣指的是短時期內的大氣變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Weather is what the atmosphere does in the short term--
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.93,0:19:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,可能是幾小時 也可能是幾天\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}hour to hour, day to day.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.06,0:19:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,天氣是變化莫測的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Weather is chaotic, which means that even
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.73,0:19:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,這意味著即使是微小的干擾也能引起大規模的變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a microscopic disturbance can lead to large-scale changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.74,0:19:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是為什麼對十天後的天氣預測是沒有用的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's why those ten-day weather forecasts are useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.61,0:19:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,巴厘島上的一隻蝴蝶扇動了翅膀 六周以後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A butterfly flaps its wings in Bali, and six weeks later,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.11,0:19:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,你在緬因州的戶外婚禮就會被狂風暴雨毀掉了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}your outdoor wedding in Maine is ruined.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.75,0:19:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,氣候研究的則是長時期的天氣的平均變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Climate is the long-term average
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.75,0:19:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,跨越幅度有好幾年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the weather, over a number of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.95,0:19:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,它是由這個星球上能改變大氣能量平衡的力量決定的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's shaped by global forces that alter the energy balance
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.59,0:19:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,比如說 陽光的變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the atmosphere, such as changes in the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.66,0:19:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,地球自轉軸的傾斜度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the tilt of the Earth's axis,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.33,0:19:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,地球反射回太空的日照量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the amount of sunlight the Earth reflects back to space
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.13,0:20:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,空氣中的溫室氣體濃度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the concentration of greenhouse gases in the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.40,0:20:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,它們當中任何一個的變化都能影響氣候\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A change in any of them affects the climate
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.73,0:20:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,而且它們的變化方式是大致可以預測的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in ways that are broadly predictable.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.34,0:20:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我的這位小朋友忽左忽右的走路方式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}My friend's meandering
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.30,0:20:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,就好比是短期的波動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}represents the short-term fluctuations--
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.44,0:20:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是天氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that's weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.08,0:20:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,基本上很難預測\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's almost impossible to predict
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.64,0:20:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,誰知道它等會兒又會對什麼感興趣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}what'll attract his interest next,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.48,0:20:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,不過我們不難知道它遊蕩的範圍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but not hard to know what the range of his meandering will be,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.58,0:20:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,因為我用皮帶牽著它\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}because I'm holding him on a leash.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.02,0:20:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,人不能直接觀察到氣候\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We can't observe climate directly--
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.52,0:20:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,因為我們所見的是天氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}all we see is the weather--
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.36,0:20:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,但經過好幾年後推算出的平均天氣變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but the average weather, over the course of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.36,0:20:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,會揭示出一個模式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}reveals a pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.03,0:20:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是一個長期的趨勢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I represent that long-term trend,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.46,0:20:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是氣候\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which is climate.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.63,0:20:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,把注意力放在人身上 別看狗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Keep your eye on the man, not the dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.17,0:20:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,天氣很難預測 就像我的這位小朋友\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Weather is hard to predict, like my friend here,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.51,0:20:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,但氣候是可以預測的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but climate is predictable.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.11,0:20:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,在地球漫長的歷史上 氣候曾經變換過好多次\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Climate has changed many times in the long history of the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.18,0:20:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,每一次都是受某種全球性力量作用的結果\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but always in response to a global force.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.85,0:20:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,現在影響氣候變化最強的力量就是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The strongest force driving climate change right now
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.19,0:21:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,由於燃燒化石燃料而不斷增加的二氧化碳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is the increasing CO2 from the burning of fossil fuels,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.19,0:21:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,它留住了更多的太陽熱量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which is trapping more heat from the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.53,0:21:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,這些多出來的能量必須有個去處\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}All that additional energy has to go somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.36,0:21:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,有些能量讓空氣升溫\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Some of it warms the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.20,0:21:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,大部分的能量則被海洋吸收\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Most of it ends up in the oceans.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.30,0:21:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,全世界的海洋現在都在變暖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}All over the world, the oceans are getting warmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.57,0:21:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,最明顯的就是北冰洋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's most obvious in the Arctic Ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.01,0:21:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,以及它周圍的陸地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the lands that surround it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.48,0:21:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 如果說我們正在失去一些夏季的海冰\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Okay, so we're losing the summer sea ice
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.48,0:21:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,不過那個地方又是沒什麼人去的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in a place where hardly anyone ever goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.08,0:21:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我幹嘛要關心北極有沒有冰呢？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What do I care if there's no ice around the North Pole?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.83,0:21:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,冰是地球最亮的自然表面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Ice is the brightest natural surface on the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.83,0:21:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,廣闊的海洋則是最暗的自然表面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and open ocean water is the darkest.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.77,0:21:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,冰能把陽光反射回太空\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Ice reflects incoming sunlight back to space.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.37,0:21:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,水則會吸收陽光而變暖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Water absorbs sunlight
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.44,0:21:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,這會讓更多的冰融化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and gets warmer, which melts even more ice,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.78,0:22:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,讓更多的海洋水面暴露出來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which exposes still more ocean surface
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.05,0:22:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,並吸收更多的陽光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to absorb even more sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.05,0:22:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是所謂的正反饋效應\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is what we call a positive feedback loop.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.52,0:22:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,這是能把二氧化碳引起的熱效應放大的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's one of many natural mechanisms that magnify
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.29,0:22:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,許多種自然機制中的一個\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}any warming caused by CO2 alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.43,0:22:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,我們現在是在阿拉斯加的德魯角\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We're at Drew Point, Alaska,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.70,0:22:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,這裏是北冰洋的邊緣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on the edge of the Arctic Ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.30,0:22:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,當我出生的時候 這裏的海岸線伸出去有1英里多\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When I was born, the shoreline was a mile farther out,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.20,0:22:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,它過去曾以每年20英尺的速度縮減\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and it was breaking off at a rate of about 20 feet per year.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.24,0:22:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,現在……\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.24,0:22:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,縮減的速度達到了每年50英尺\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it's being eaten away at about 50 feet per year.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.41,0:22:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,北冰洋正在變暖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Arctic Ocean is warming
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.41,0:22:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,而且變暖的速度在不斷增快\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and at an increasing rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.78,0:22:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,所以每年裏有大部分時間這裏是沒有冰的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So it's ice-free during more of the year.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.88,0:22:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,有更多的海岸線因此暴露出來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That leaves the shore here
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.89,0:22:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,被風暴所侵蝕\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}more exposed to erosion from storms,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.42,0:22:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,這讓另一種力量變得更強大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which are also getting more powerful,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.76,0:23:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,這種力量能影響氣候的變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}another effect of climate change.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.96,0:23:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,阿拉斯加北部 西伯利亞 加拿大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The northern reaches of Alaska, Siberia and Canada
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.96,0:23:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,這些地方的大部分是永久性凍土\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are mostly permafrost,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.83,0:23:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,地面被凍結超過千年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}ground that has been frozen year-round for millennia.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.27,0:23:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,它裏面含有很多有機質\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It contains lots of organic matter,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.10,0:23:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,過去的樹葉與樹根\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}old leaves and roots from plants
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.84,0:23:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,它們曾生長在數千年前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that grew thousands of years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.01,0:23:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,由於北冰洋地區的升溫速度在加快\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Because the Arctic regions are warming faster
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.01,0:23:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,比地球上其他地區都要快\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}than anywhere else on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.95,0:23:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,永久性凍土開始融化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the permafrost is thawing
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.02,0:23:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,凍土中的東西開始腐爛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and its contents are rotting,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.02,0:23:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,效果就和冰箱斷電差不多\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}just like when you unplug the freezer.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.53,0:23:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,融化的凍土釋放出二氧化碳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The thawing permafrost is releasing carbon dioxide
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.96,0:23:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,還有甲烷 這是一種更厲害的的溫室氣體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and methane, an even more potent greenhouse gas,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.53,0:23:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,它們都進入了大氣中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.30,0:23:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,這讓世界變得更熱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is making things even warmer,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.70,0:23:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,還有一個正反饋效應的例子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}another example of a positive feedback mechanism.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.37,0:23:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,世界的永久性凍土層中儲存有大量的碳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The world's permafrost stores enough carbon
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.14,0:23:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,足以讓大氣中的二氧化碳再增加一倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to more than double the CO2 in the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.71,0:23:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,按照現在的速度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}At the rate we're going,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.05,0:23:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,全球變暖很快就要實現大部分了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}global warming could release most of it
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.65,0:23:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,時間就是本世紀末\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}by the end of the century.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.38,0:24:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,人類也許正在將氣候推上一條不歸路\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We might be tipping the climate past a point of no return
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.82,0:24:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,讓它走向無法預知的一面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into an unpredictable slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.46,0:24:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 如果空氣 水 陸地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Okay, the air, the water
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.29,0:24:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,還有其他的一切都變暖了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the land are all getting warmer,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.63,0:24:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,全球變暖真的發生了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}so global warming is really happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.47,0:24:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,也許這不是人類的錯\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But maybe it's not our fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.63,0:24:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,也許這是自然造成的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Maybe it's just nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.70,0:24:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,也許是因為太陽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Maybe it's the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.21,0:24:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,不 也許不是因為太陽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No, it's not the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.31,0:24:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,我們這幾十年來一直在密切的觀測太陽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We've been monitoring the Sun very closely for decades,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.65,0:24:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,而太陽輸送的能量一直都沒有變過\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the solar energy output hasn't changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.49,0:24:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,還有 地球現在是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What's more, the Earth is warming more at night
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.32,0:24:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,晚上比白天更暖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}than in daytime,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.49,0:24:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,冬天比夏天更暖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and more in winter than in summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.33,0:24:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,這是符合溫室效應規律的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's exactly what we expect from greenhouse warming,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.76,0:24:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,與太陽輸送能量的增加\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but the opposite of what increased solar output
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.03,0:24:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,一點關係都沒有\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}would cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.07,0:24:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,懷疑是沒有用的 現在的一切清楚表明\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's now clear beyond any reasonable doubt
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.31,0:24:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,人類正在改變氣候\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that we are changing the climate.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.04,0:24:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽根本就不是元兇\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Sun isn't the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.04,0:24:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,而拯救這一切的方案\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But it is the solution,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.88,0:24:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,人類早已制備了很久\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and we've known this for a long time,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.08,0:25:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,早在比你想像中更久遠的年代\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}much longer than you might think.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.26,0:25:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,巴黎 1878年9月\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Paris, September 1878.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.83,0:25:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,埃菲爾鐵塔還要過好多年才會開始建造\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Eiffel Tower won't be built for years to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.77,0:25:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.50,0:25:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}世博會
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.61,0:25:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,世界上最壯觀非凡的景象\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the world has ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.64,0:25:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,自由女神像宏偉的頭部\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The magnificent head of the Statue of Liberty
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.91,0:25:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,才剛剛造好\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}has just been completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.59,0:25:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,全球各地數千家展商\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Thousands of exhibitors from around the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.86,0:25:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,在巴黎的66英畝土地上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}covered 66 acres of Paris
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.09,0:25:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,佈滿了他們的發明與產品\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with their inventions and goods.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.40,0:25:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,愛迪生發明的燈泡還要在好幾年後才\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Edison's first public demonstration of the light bulb
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.40,0:25:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,第一次向公眾展示\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}will not take place for another year.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.07,0:25:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,電氣設備還沒有出現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's no such thing as electrical appliances.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.97,0:25:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,人們還不會開開關 按按鈕\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}People don't flick switches and press buttons.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.97,0:25:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,這是一個人牽馬拉的世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's a hand-cranked, horse-drawn world.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.98,0:26:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是我們要說到的那個人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's the guy we came to see,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.65,0:26:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,那個有奇怪鬍子的人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the one with the crazy moustache.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.49,0:26:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,他是一個數學老師 名叫奧古斯丁•莫超\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He's a math teacher named Augustin Mouchot.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.53,0:26:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,記住 這是在1878年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Remember, it's 1878.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.00,0:26:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,一個由煤氣燈統治的世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is a world lit mostly by gaslight.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.47,0:26:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,汽車還要過好多年才會發明\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The automobile is still years away.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.87,0:26:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,但莫超的發明足以讓觀眾目瞪口呆\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But Mouchot, here, is dazzling the crowd
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.67,0:26:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,那是一個太陽能聚能設備\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with his solar power concentrator.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.68,0:26:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽屬於我們每一個人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Sun belongs to all of us!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.98,0:26:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,就算它距離我們1億5千萬公里遠\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Even though it is 150 million kilometers away from us,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.18,0:26:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,感受一下它那強悍的威力吧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}feel its awesome power!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.35,0:26:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我的發明能把太陽散發的免費的能量集中起來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}My invention concentrates the free energy of the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.36,0:26:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,把它轉化為機械運動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and converts it into mechanical motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.36,0:26:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,為任何一種機器提供能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It can power any kind of machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.00,0:26:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,它可以用來發電或者是讓印刷機運轉\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It can produce electricity or run a printing press
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.37,0:26:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,甚至是在熱天製冰\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}or make ice on a hot day.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.81,0:26:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,等著瞧吧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Et voila !
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.38,0:27:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,想想吧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.49,0:27:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,既然陽光能轉化為冰塊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}sunlight converted into ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.92,0:27:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,想想吧 朋友們 如果我們能把豐富的太陽能利用起來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You see, my friends, what wonders we can work
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.76,0:27:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我們能做出什麼樣的奇跡來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}if we harness the bounteous energy of the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.93,0:27:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,世界上的煤總有一天會用完\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The world will someday run out of coal,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.73,0:27:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,但輝煌的太陽永遠在那裏照耀著我們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but the magnificent Sun will always be there for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.42,0:27:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,莫超獲得了這一屆世界博覽會的金獎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Mouchot took home the gold medal from the fair.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.92,0:27:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,但煤炭的價格下跌了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But the price of coal tumbled,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.75,0:27:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,價格如此之低以至於人們對太陽能再也沒有興趣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}becoming so cheap that there was no interest in solar energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.26,0:27:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,此外 當時還沒有人明白\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Besides, no one understood, back then,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.03,0:27:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,燃燒化石燃料的真正代價是什麼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}what the true cost was of burning fossil fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.76,0:27:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,莫超的研究經費被砍掉了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Mouchot's research funding was cut off.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.93,0:27:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,35年後 也就是二十世紀初期\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}35 years later, in the early years of the 20th century,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.37,0:28:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,通向另一個未來的另一扇大門被打開了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}another door opened to an alternative future.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.04,0:28:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,它發生在埃及 尼羅河岸邊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It happened in Egypt, on the banks of the Nile.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.81,0:28:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,未來的時間旅行者們記住了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Memo to future time travelers...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.81,0:28:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,這是一個對避免氣候變化而言\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}this would be an excellent entry point
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.15,0:28:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,絕佳的起點\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for averting climate change.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.25,0:28:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,1913年 埃及\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Egypt, 1913.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.26,0:28:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,這是來自美國費城的弗蘭克•舒曼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's Frank Shuman of Philadelphia.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.09,0:28:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,他只讀過3年書\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He's only had three years of schooling,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.43,0:28:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,但他天才的創造發明能力彌補了這一切\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but his genius for innovation more than makes up for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.43,0:28:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,在30歲以前 舒曼發明了安全玻璃\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Before he was 30, Shuman had invented safety glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.50,0:28:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,它被廣泛用在汽車與飛機上 挽救了無數的生命\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Its use in automobiles and skylights saved countless lives
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.34,0:28:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,也讓他變得非常有錢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and made him a very rich man,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.68,0:28:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,有錢 讓他能去追求自己真正的夢想\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}rich enough to pursue his real passion,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.62,0:28:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽能\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}solar energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.85,0:28:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,舒曼領導著一支團隊設計並建造了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Shuman led the team that designed and built
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.12,0:29:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,一組太陽能聚能設備\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}an array of solar energy concentrators.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.36,0:29:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,它能驅動蒸汽機\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It could power a steam engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.86,0:29:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,舒曼希望利用太陽能\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Shuman is hoping to use the Sun's power
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.03,0:29:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,以灌溉沙漠\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to irrigate the desert
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.63,0:29:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,讓它重新變綠\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and turn it green.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.47,0:29:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,舒曼的太陽能發電站\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The official inauguration
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.10,0:29:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,在1913年正式啟動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of Shuman's solar power plant, in 1913,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.10,0:29:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,這是個了不起的成就\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was a dazzling success.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.14,0:29:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,他發明了一種實用的方法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He had invented a practical way to tap the Sun's energy
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.88,0:29:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,讓太陽能得以實現工業規模的應用\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on an industrial scale,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.52,0:29:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,讓太陽能比煤更便宜\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}making solar energy even cheaper than coal.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.29,0:29:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,英德兩國政府\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The British and German governments
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.79,0:29:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,給予了舒曼慷慨的贊助\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}both offered Shuman generous funding
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.79,0:29:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,讓他去創造發明\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to develop his invention.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.70,0:29:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,這是一種理想的豐富的能量來源\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was the ideal source of abundant power
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.73,0:29:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,尤其是在熱帶地區\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in tropical regions,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.73,0:29:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,那裏進口煤的價格比較昂貴\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}where imported coal was prohibitively expensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.57,0:29:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,但舒曼有更大的夢想\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But Shuman was dreaming even bigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.34,0:29:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,在給《科學美國人》寫的一封信中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In a letter to Scientific American,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.74,0:29:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,他對他的太陽能發電廠進行了計算\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he calculated that his solar power plants,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.58,0:29:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,如果能將它安裝在一個像撒哈拉沙漠那樣的地區\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}if deployed in an area of the Sahara Desert
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.92,0:30:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,只需要方圓150英里的面積 就能提供\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}only 150 miles on a side, could supply as much power
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.99,0:30:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,足以讓世界所有工廠消費的能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as consumed by all the industries of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.16,0:30:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,但這一切最終沒有發生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But it was not to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.16,0:30:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,石油 這種液體化石燃料的市場\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The market for a liquid fossil fuel, petroleum,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.26,0:30:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,隨船運而蓬勃發展起來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was exploding for shipping,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.10,0:30:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,家庭供熱 汽車與卡車\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}home heating, and cars and trucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.73,0:30:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,石油很豐富 甚至比煤還便宜\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Oil was abundant, cheaper even than coal,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.40,0:30:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,它很容易就能獲得 易於加工\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and much easier to get out of the ground and process.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.31,0:30:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,要把煤裝滿一艘船 需要100個人幹上1周\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It took 100 men a week to fuel a ship with coal,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.81,0:30:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,但如果是裝石油\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but with oil, one man could do the job
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.35,0:30:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,1個人幹上1天就可以了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in a single day.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.01,0:30:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,舒曼在沙漠中取得成功後的第2年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A year after Shuman's triumph in the desert,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.85,0:30:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,第一次世界大戰爆發\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}World War I broke out.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.69,0:30:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,他的太陽能集熱器被回收 變成了武器\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}His solar collectors were recycled into weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.46,0:30:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,舒曼夢想中的太陽能發電的文明社會\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Frank Shuman's dream of a solar-powered civilization
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.53,0:30:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,只有等到下一個世紀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}would have to wait another century
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.37,0:30:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,才能獲得重生的機遇\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}before it was reborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.14,0:30:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,在我們這個世界上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's another inexhaustible source of clean energy
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.57,0:30:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,還有另一種取之不盡的清潔能源\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.24,0:30:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,風能本身也是由太陽能產生的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The winds themselves are solar-powered,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.35,0:31:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽驅動著風與波浪\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}because our star drives the winds and the waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.75,0:31:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,與太陽能集熱器不同\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Unlike solar collectors,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.52,0:31:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,風能發電廠只需要很少的土地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}wind farms take up very little land,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.69,0:31:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,如果是在海邊 那就一點陸地都用不到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and none at all, if offshore,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.99,0:31:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,海上的風力是最強的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}where the winds are strongest.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.03,0:31:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,如果人類能把世界上百分之一的風能利用起來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If we could tap even one percent of their power,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.90,0:31:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,就會有充足的能源供文明社會運作\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we'd have enough energy to run our civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.11,0:31:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,而每個小時落在地球上的太陽能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And more solar energy falls on Earth in one hour
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.45,0:31:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,都超過我們人類社會\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}than all the energy our civilization consumes
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.09,0:31:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,1年消費的能量總和\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in an entire year.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.96,0:31:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,只要人類能把很小一部分\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If we could harness a tiny fraction
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.76,0:31:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,可用的太陽能與風能利用起來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the available solar and wind power,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.89,0:31:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,人類就會有永久充足的能源供應\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we could supply all our energy needs forever,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.06,0:31:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,而無需向大氣中排放任何的碳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and without adding any carbon to the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.64,0:32:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,現在時猶未晚\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's not too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.81,0:32:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,未來仍值得我們奮鬥\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's a future worth fighting for.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.91,0:32:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,為何我能這樣肯定？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How do I know?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.58,0:32:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我們每個人都是艱苦鬥爭後的倖存者\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Every one of us comes from a long line of survivors.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.95,0:32:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,如果不懂得適應環境 人類這個物種就不會存在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our species is nothing if not adaptive.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.59,0:32:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,因為我們的先人學會了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was only because our ancestors learned
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.12,0:32:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,目光長遠 應時而動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to think long-term, and act accordingly,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.99,0:32:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,人類才會有今天\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that we're here at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.83,0:32:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,前有困阻 但我們不能退避\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We've had our backs to the wall before,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.93,0:32:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,我們要邁向新的高度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and we came through to scale new heights.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.07,0:32:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,實際上 人類歷史上所取得的很多偉大的成就\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In fact, the most mythic human accomplishments of all
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.60,0:32:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,都是來自最黑暗的時刻\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}came out of our darkest hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.74,0:32:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,曾經有這樣一個世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Once there was a world
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.45,0:32:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,6萬枚核武器如箭在弦上 時刻待發\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}rigged with 60,000hair-triggered nuclear weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.95,0:32:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,這場廝殺發生在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The combatants were
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.59,0:32:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,地球上兩個最強大的國家之間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the two most powerful countries on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.26,0:32:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,他們死也要纏在一起\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and they were locked in a deadly embrace,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.42,0:32:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,每一個國家都宣稱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}each vowing that they would rather see
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.03,0:32:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,寧願讓這個世界玉石俱焚\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}everything we love destroyed
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.93,0:32:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,也不要不讓別人得到她\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}than submit to the will of the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.50,0:33:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,當時我才3歲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When I was three years old,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.50,0:33:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,有史以來威力最強的人造炸彈\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the largest man-made explosion of all time
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.07,0:33:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,剛由蘇聯引爆\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was detonated by the Soviet Union.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.65,0:33:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,舊的恐懼剛剛消退 新的恐懼隨之而來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That terror has subsided, to be replaced by new fears.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.82,0:33:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,地球上2000個最大的城市\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The danger that the 2,000 largest cities on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.55,0:33:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,隨時會有在一個下午內化為廢墟的危險\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}would be reduced to rubble in the space of an afternoon
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.62,0:33:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,但跟這個比都算不上什麼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is no longer one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.62,0:33:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,美國與蘇聯之間的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The nuclear rivalry between the United States
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.29,0:33:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,核軍備競賽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the Soviet Union
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.33,0:33:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,創造了一個副產品\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}had another by-product.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.63,0:33:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,阿波羅登月計劃\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Apollo missions to the Moon were an extension
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.74,0:33:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,就是美蘇間軍備競爭的產物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the arms race that raged between them.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.47,0:33:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,把人送上地球軌道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Sending people to orbit the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.57,0:33:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,或是送到月球 都需要大型的 可靠的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}or go to the Moon requires big, reliable,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.64,0:33:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,大推力火箭 而這正是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}powerful rockets-- precisely the same technology
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.05,0:33:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,攜帶核彈頭所需的科技\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}you need to carry a nuclear warhead
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.82,0:33:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,讓它可以飛越半個地球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}halfway around the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.39,0:33:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,摧毀敵國的最大城市\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to destroy your enemy's largest cities.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.53,0:33:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,我相信這個國家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}"I believe that this nation
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.36,0:33:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,一定會達成這個目標\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}should commit itself to achieving the goal,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.56,0:34:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,那就是在未來的十年裏 把人送上月球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}before this decade is out, of landing a man on the Moon
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.40,0:34:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,並讓他安全的返回地球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and returning him safely to the Earth."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.84,0:34:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,肯尼迪總統1961年的演講\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}President Kennedy's 1961 speech
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.61,0:34:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,讓這個國家興奮起來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}electrified the nation,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.94,0:34:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,裏面提到了很多讓人印象深刻的遠景計劃\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and it contained much that was remarkably prophetic--
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.35,0:34:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,但在關於探月計劃的內容中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but not a word about a scientific objective
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.85,0:34:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有一個字是跟科學項目有關的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for going to the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.85,0:34:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有關於對月球起源的探索\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No questions about the Moon's origin
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.12,0:34:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,或是帶回樣品進行分析的想法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}or the hope of bringing back samples to analyze.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.26,0:34:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,阿波羅計劃與科學無關 它原本就是為了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No, the Apollo missions were conceived
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.13,0:34:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,展示超級大國的實力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as a demonstration of the superior power
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.53,0:34:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,以及戰術導彈的精度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and precision of our strategic missiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.56,0:34:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,但可笑的是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But a funny thing happened to us...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.90,0:34:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,在探月的道路上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on our way to the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.44,0:34:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,當人類回望故鄉時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We looked homeward...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.74,0:34:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,卻發現了另一個世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and discovered another world--
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.91,0:34:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我們自己的世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.58,0:34:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,第一次 我們這些地球的居民\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For the first time, we inhabitants of Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.91,0:34:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,可以後退一步 看看地球到底是什麼樣子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}could step back and see it as it really is--
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.09,0:34:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,這是一個不可分割的世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}one world, indivisible,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.69,0:34:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,在浩瀚的宇宙中它是如此的渺小\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and kind of small in the cosmic context.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.29,0:35:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,不管是為了什麼原因 讓我們集結了大量的資源\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Whatever the reason we first mustered the enormous resources
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.26,0:35:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,投入到阿波羅計劃上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}required for the Apollo program,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.70,0:35:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,不管冷戰時期的我們是如何深陷民族主義的思潮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}however mired it was in Cold War nationalism
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.53,0:35:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,以及對殺人武器的追求\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the instruments of death,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.60,0:35:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,我們仍不可避免地認識到了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the inescapable recognition of the unity
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.61,0:35:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,地球是脆弱而不可分割的統一體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and fragility of the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.61,0:35:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,每一個明亮發光的點都是它的組成部分\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is its clear and luminous dividend,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.14,0:35:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,這是阿波羅計劃的意外收穫\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the unexpected gift of Apollo.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.61,0:35:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,一個致力於死亡競賽的項目\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A project conceived in deadly competition
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.82,0:35:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,讓我們認識了這個地球共同體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}made us recognize our community.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.30,0:35:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,是什麼樣的巨人修建了這個世界奇觀？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What titan built this wonder of the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.07,0:35:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,是菲律賓伊富高省的人民\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was the Ifugao people of the Philippines,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.11,0:35:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,依靠著他們的雙手辛勤勞作\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}working with not much more than their hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.38,0:35:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,在大約1萬年前 我們在世界各地的祖先\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}About 10,000 years ago, our ancestors all over the world
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.05,0:35:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,利用了另一種形式的氣候突變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}took advantage of another form of climate change,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.62,0:35:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,冰河時代間歇期中出現的溫和天氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the gentler climate of the intermission in the ice age--
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.89,0:36:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,他們發明了農業\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they invented agriculture.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.46,0:36:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,他們放棄了無休止的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They gave up the ceaseless wandering,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.63,0:36:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,流浪 遊獵以及採集的生活方式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}hunting and gathering that had been their way of life
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.93,0:36:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,這種方式曾延續了1百萬年之久\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for a million years or so,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.93,0:36:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,他們定居下來 生產食物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to settle down and produce food.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.54,0:36:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,他們發現耕作農田\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They found a way to harvest
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.06,0:36:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,能讓他們比先人通過自然環境\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}ten to a hundred times more solar energy
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.96,0:36:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,獲得要高出十到百倍之多的太陽能\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}than the environment naturally provided for their ancestors.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.76,0:36:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,世界各地的人們艱難地實現了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}People all over the world made the difficult transition
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.30,0:36:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,從遊牧文化向農耕文化的轉變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from nomadic cultures to agricultural ones
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.60,0:36:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,這是一種更有效的使用太陽能的方式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that used solar energy more efficiently.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.84,0:36:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,這讓文明興盛起來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It gave rise to civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.48,0:36:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,我們就站在那些辛勤勞作的先人的肩上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We stand on the shoulders of those who did the hard work
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.05,0:36:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,他們為我們實現最基礎的轉變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that such a fundamental transformation required.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.65,0:36:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,現在 該輪到我們了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Now... it's our turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.89,0:36:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,曾經有這樣一個世界……\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Once there was a world...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.30,0:37:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,如果在金星上曾有過生命 他們也不會有機會\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If life ever existed on Venus, it would have had no chance
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.24,0:37:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,扭轉這個世界走向地獄的命運\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to avert the hellish destiny of this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.48,0:37:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,這種失控的溫室效應是無法阻擋的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This runaway greenhouse effect was unstoppable.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.49,0:37:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,曾經\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Once...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.26,0:37:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,有這樣一個世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}there was a world...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.47,0:37:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,那是我們的世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.63,0:37:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,就是現在的世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And that world is now.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.30,0:37:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有任何科學或技術上的障礙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There are no scientific or technological obstacles
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.81,0:37:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,會阻止我們保護這個世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to protecting our world
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.68,0:37:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,保護這個世界上珍貴的生命\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the precious life that it supports.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.15,0:37:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,一切都取決於\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It all depends...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.05,0:37:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我們真正珍惜的是什麼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on what we truly value...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.05,0:37:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我們能否付諸於行動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and if we can summon the will to act.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.33,0:38:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,"為什麼" 有人問 為什麼要選擇月亮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But why, some say, the Moon?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.53,0:38:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,為什麼把它作為我們的目標？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Why choose this as our goal?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.70,0:38:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,他們也許還會問\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And they may well ask,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.84,0:38:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我們為什麼要登上世界的最高峰？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}why climb the highest mountain?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.34,0:38:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,而我們選擇了登月\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We choose to go to the Moon...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.25,0:39:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我們選擇了在十年內登月\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}...we choose to go to the Moon in this decade
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.82,0:39:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,我們還要做其他的事情\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and do the other things,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.69,0:39:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,不是因為它們很容易 而是因為它們很難\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}not because they are easy, but because they are hard.
